# Mock test authoring

## No image-based questions

Mock tests must **not** use image stimuli. Students answer from text only.

**Prohibited fields and patterns:**

- `content.imageUrl`, `content.pictureSequence`, `content.imageOptions`
- Choice `mediaUrl` pointing to images
- Question types `image_selection`, `mcq_image`
- Stems that require viewing a picture without a text scene (e.g. "Look at the picture" with no `taskDescription`)

**Use instead:**

| Former pattern | Text-only replacement |
|----------------|----------------------|
| Picture MCQ / listening tick-the-picture | Text choices; stem: "Choose the best answer" |
| Word–picture matching | Word–description matching (`rightText` describes the item) |
| Writing from a picture | `taskDescription: "Scene: …"` with a clear text scene |
| Speaking spot-the-difference | `taskDescription` with **Scene A** / **Scene B** paragraphs |
| Speaking story from pictures | `taskDescription` with numbered **Story outline** beats |
| KET/PET photo description | `taskDescription: "Scene: …"` describing the setting |

## Helpers

- Gold mocks: `goldWriting()`, `goldSpeaking()`, `goldMcq()` from `gold-mock-helpers.ts`
- Do not pass `imageUrl`, `pictureSequence`, or `imageOptions` to helpers
- Practice mocks: follow `docs/mock-tests/m1-yle-practice-mock-authoring.md`

## Quality

- One learning objective per item; age-appropriate language
- MCQ distractors plausible and same category as the key
- Writing/speaking tasks must be evaluable without image context (M2.2 / M2.3 rubrics)
- Run `npm run test -- gold-mock.validation` before seeding

